# Syncthing ignore patterns for a home-directory-rooted folder share.
# Goal: sync only Claude Code's runtime state (history/sessions/settings/
# credentials), skip everything else in the home directory, and skip the
# parts of .claude/ that are machine-bound or purely regenerable.
#
# Paste this into the Syncthing folder's "Ignore Patterns" editor (or drop
# this file as `.stignore` at the root of the shared folder), then use
# Syncthing's "Preview" to confirm the actual file list before trusting it -
# ignore-pattern precedence can vary slightly by Syncthing version.

# 1) Ignore everything in the home directory by default...
*

# 2) ...except Claude Code's state.
!/.claude
!/.claude/**
!/.claude.json
!/.claude.json.backup

# 3) Within .claude/, re-exclude machine-bound / regenerable subpaths.
#    (Plugins are intentionally excluded - see SYNC.md: they carry
#    machine-specific absolute paths and are re-installed automatically
#    from settings.json instead of being file-synced.)
/.claude/plugins/**
/.claude/daemon/**
/.claude/shell-snapshots/**
/.claude/cache/**
/.claude/daemon.log
/.claude/.last-cleanup
/.claude/.last-update-result.json
